# Mixed GeoSPARQL features around the Schependomlaan / Waalbrug site in Nijmegen.
#
# A small "all the 2D geometry types" sample for the map viewer: a POINT, a
# LINESTRING and a POLYGON, each a real geo:Feature with a geo:hasGeometry /
# geo:asWKT GeoSPARQL geometry. Coordinates are WGS84 lon/lat (CRS84, the
# GeoSPARQL default — no <crs> prefix needed), so they pass straight through the
# viewer feed's reprojection onto the map. These exercise the GeoSPARQL geof:
# relation/measurement functions (sfWithin, distance, …) and the 2D map layers.
#
# Coordinates are plausible real-world positions near the Schependomlaan block
# (≈ 5.834 E, 51.841 N); the LINESTRING traces the street, the POLYGON a small
# park parcel beside it.

@prefix rdfs:    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix geo:     <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#> .
@prefix gf:      <https://opentriplestore.org/demo/viewer-3d-demo/features#> .

# ── A point of interest: the Schependomlaan street centroid ──
gf:SchependomlaanPoint a geo:Feature ;
    rdfs:label "Schependomlaan (street centroid)"@en ;
    dcterms:type "point-of-interest" ;
    geo:hasGeometry [ a geo:Geometry ;
        geo:asWKT "POINT(5.83373 51.84114)"^^geo:wktLiteral ] .

# ── A linear feature: the Schependomlaan street alignment ──
gf:SchependomlaanRoad a geo:Feature ;
    rdfs:label "Schependomlaan (alignment)"@en ;
    dcterms:type "road-centreline" ;
    geo:hasGeometry [ a geo:Geometry ;
        geo:asWKT "LINESTRING(5.83210 51.84060, 5.83373 51.84114, 5.83540 51.84168)"^^geo:wktLiteral ] .

# ── An areal feature: a small park parcel beside the block ──
gf:KwakkenbergPark a geo:Feature ;
    rdfs:label "Park parcel (Schependomlaan)"@en ;
    dcterms:type "green-space" ;
    geo:hasGeometry [ a geo:Geometry ;
        geo:asWKT "POLYGON((5.83420 51.84150, 5.83520 51.84150, 5.83520 51.84200, 5.83420 51.84200, 5.83420 51.84150))"^^geo:wktLiteral ] .
